SageAttention disabled by default, if you're systems supports that enable it. 
If you enabled it and wish to disable, you have to change sage_attention in the node to disabled and run your workflow again in order for it to disable

At the time of updating this workflow, Skip Layer Guidance doesn't work. 
Try to re enable it from time to time, might've been fixed.

Select the correct model_type for TeaCache to work! 
The unet_name in the Load Diffusion Model node should match the model_type in the TeaCache node.

Lower max_skip_steps if you're getting lack of motion or artifacts

I found that for TeaCache, higher shift and higher steps provide much better results, experiment as you wish.
